OL,3,C'I just want people to remember how
OL,4,Cclose it is': says Ukrainian filmmaker
OL,6,FIt can't be easy to inhabit such
OL,7,Fdifferent worlds; to tread the red
OL,8,Fcarpet one moment and then to cower in
OL,9,Fa muddy trench.
OL,11,F"It is a paradox,'' he says. "The
OL,12,Fexistence of those red carpets in
OL,13,Fnormal life... and then you travel
OL,14,Facross a couple thousands of
OL,15,Fkilometres and you just cross the
OL,16,Fborder, take a train, take a car, and
OL,17,Fyou are back in time 100 years.
OL,19,F"Or sometimes it feels like another
OL,20,Fplanet. It's so different.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
